trans-unit.source: The cost (also called metric) of an interface in OSPF is an indication of the overhead required to send packets across a certain interface. The formula used to calculate the cost is cost= 10000 0000/bandwith in bps For example, it will cost 10 EXP8/10 EXP7 = 10 to cross a 10M Ethernet line and will cost 10 EXP8/1544000 = 64 to cross a T1 line.
